@BoomBots2 @NJDeptofHealth Sorry hit you are just wrong.

A side effect is only considered as such when there is a causal link established between the vaccine and an AE. Then it becomes an “adverse reaction”.

The nine pages are just “stuff Pfizer was monitoring”. The longer the better.

@Hicksyfern @NJDeptofHealth If it is a "pre-specified medically-significant event" that is a side effect.

It is a side effect of a vaccine "that needs to be carefully monitored and confirmed."

Regardless, the fact that theres 9 pages of side effects and AESI's is not good. No matter how you spin it.
